   Over 44 million people in the United States lack access to primary
   health care. HRSA assures that uderserved and vulnerable people get the
   health care they need. Through a nationwide network of primary health
   care programs that include Community and Migrant Health Centers, Health
   Care for the Homeless, National Health Services Corps, Immigration
   Health Services, and Models That Work, HRSA is assuring that
   underserved and vulnerable populations get the health care they need.
