   First Gov site Primary Care Programs Directory 2001
   Provides a listing of organizations funded under one or more of the
   following nine Federal Grant programs administered by the Bureau of
   Primary Health Care: Black Lung Clinics, Community Health Centers,
   Federally Qualified Health Center Look-Alikes, Health Care for the
   Homeless, Healthy Schools Healthy Communities, Migrant Health Centers,
   National Health Service Corps Supported Sites, Outreach and Primary
   Health Services for Homeless Children, Public Housing Primary Care.
   Includes satellite sites of clinics affiliated with each grantee and an
   index listing of each clinic by State.
   - Healthy Schools, Healthy Communities Program Directory
   Directory provides a synopsis of 76 school-based health center programs
   funded by the Health Resources and Services Administration's (HRSA)
   Bureau of Primary Health Care (BPHC) under the HSHC Program.
   School-based centers highlighted in this directory provide a
   comprehensive array of services to children and adolescents who might
   not ordinarily have access to primary health care and mental services.
   - Changing Lives, Changing Communities Through Primary Health Care
   Learn about the many programs offered by the Bureau for Primary Health
   Care to help ensure that the people of our Nation receive adequate
   health care. Programs described include the National Health Service
   Corps and grant programs to fund community-based Health Centers (e.g.,
   Community Health Centers; Migrant Health Centers; Health Care for the
   Homeless; Public Housing Primary Care Programs; and Healthy Schools,
   Healthy Communities.

